HEADWORD: Misderive
<hw>Mis`de*rive"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
turn or divert improperly; to misdirect.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To derive erroneously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

